<HTMLOptionElementIndex>
<summary>
The read-only <strong><c>index</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLOptionElement"/> interface specifies the 0-based index of the element; that is, the position of the {{HTMLElement("option")}} within the list of options it belongs to, in tree-order, as an integer. If the <c>&amp;lt;option&amp;gt;</c> is not part of an option-list, the value is <c>0</c>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/option">option</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select">select</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/datalist">datalist</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLOptionElement.DefaultSelected"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLOptionElement.Selected"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLSelectElement.SelectedIndex"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLOptionsCollection"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLOptionElement/index"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A number.</value>
</HTMLOptionElementIndex>
